Minister of Higher Education, Science and Innovation, Blade Nzimande, will release the outcome of the Human Sciences Research Council (HSRC) survey on Sunday; this is the second part of the public perception survey on the impact of the coronavirus on South Africans. This follows the first survey, conducted in March, during which the council looked at how South Africans feel about the survey, what they understand, know, and how they are reacting to the COVID-19 emergency.  The second round of the survey, which was conducted in April, looked at the lockdown as implemented from March 27th to April 16th. The results of the survey will be released during a virtual media briefing on Sunday. In the video below, the HSRC conducts a public perception survey on COVID-19 impact: 